<h2>9. My AI Front Desk</h2>
<p><strong>Overall rating: 3.6/5</strong></p>
<p><strong>Best for:</strong> Businesses that serve multilingual customers</p>
<p><strong>Pricing:</strong> $99/month for standard; custom pricing for enterprise</p>
<p>My AI Front Desk leads the market in language support. It handles 20+ languages including Spanish, Mandarin, Arabic, and Hindi. For businesses in diverse markets, this is a significant advantage.</p>
<p>The built-in CRM uses a kanban-style board to track callers through your sales process. Each caller becomes a card that moves from "New Lead" to "Qualified" to "Appointment Booked" to "Closed." This visual pipeline is intuitive and requires no separate CRM subscription.</p>
<p>Voice cloning is available on higher-tier plans. The AI can be trained to sound like you or a specific team member, adding a personal touch to automated calls.</p>
<p><strong>Pros:</strong>
- Best multilingual support in the market
- Built-in CRM with kanban board
- Voice cloning available
- Strong for diverse customer bases</p>
<p><strong>Cons:</strong>
- Higher price point
- Overkill for English-only businesses
- No free tier
- CRM is basic compared to dedicated tools</p>
<p><strong>Verdict:</strong> My AI Front Desk is the right choice if you serve customers in multiple languages. For English-only businesses, HireJosie or Smith.ai offer better value.</p>
<h2>10. Loman</h2>
<p><strong>Overall rating: 3.5/5</strong></p>
<p><strong>Best for:</strong> Restaurants that need POS-integrated phone answering</p>
<p><strong>Pricing:</strong> $199/month plus $149 setup fee</p>
<p>Loman is the only AI answering service purpose-built for restaurants. It integrates directly with Toast, Square, and Clover POS systems. The AI takes orders, books reservations, and answers menu questions.</p>
<p>The order-taking feature is impressive. A caller can place a pickup order by speaking to the AI, which enters it directly into your POS system. The AI handles modifications ("extra cheese, no onions"), calculates totals, and provides estimated pickup times.</p>
<p>Reservation booking connects to your reservation system and manages table availability. The AI can handle parties of various sizes, special requests, and time preferences.</p>
<p>The $199 price point is high for a small restaurant, but the value is clear. A single busy Friday night can generate 50+ calls. Missing 20 of those calls at an average order value of $45 means $900 in lost revenue per night.</p>
<p><strong>Pros:</strong>
- Direct POS integration
- Order taking and reservation booking
- Handles 50 simultaneous calls
- Purpose-built for restaurant workflows</p>
<p><strong>Cons:</strong>
- Highest price on this list
- Setup fee adds to initial cost
- No value outside restaurants
- Overkill for small cafes with low call volume</p>
<p><strong>Verdict:</strong> Loman is essential for busy restaurants that lose orders to voicemail. The POS integration and order-taking features justify the price for high-volume establishments.</p>
