<h2>How to Choose the Right AI Answering Service</h2>
<p>Use this decision framework:</p>
<p><strong>You need appointment booking at the lowest cost:</strong> HireJosie. The free tier lets you test, and the Pro plan is the best value in the market.</p>
<p><strong>You need human backup for complex calls:</strong> Smith.ai. The hybrid approach is expensive but unmatched for sensitive industries.</p>
<p><strong>You are a contractor or home service business:</strong> Clara. The industry-specific questioning and job summaries save hours of estimate prep.</p>
<p><strong>You receive 300+ calls per month:</strong> IsOn24 or Goodcall. Unlimited minutes or generous allowances keep costs predictable.</p>
<p><strong>You serve multilingual customers:</strong> My AI Front Desk. Twenty-plus languages and a built-in CRM justify the higher price.</p>
<p><strong>You run a busy restaurant:</strong> Loman. POS integration and order-taking are features no other service offers.</p>
<p><strong>You just need basic message taking:</strong> Upfirst or Dialzara. Both are under $30 per month and handle the essentials.</p>
<h2>What the Data Says About Missed Calls</h2>
<p>The statistics reveal why AI answering services are not a luxury. They are a necessity.</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>62%</strong> of inbound calls to small businesses go unanswered (411 Locals, 2025)</li>
<li><strong>85%</strong> of callers who reach voicemail do not leave a message (Forbes)</li>
