<h2>The 5 Mistakes That Waste Money on AI Answering Services</h2>
<p><strong>1. Choosing the cheapest option without checking features.</strong> Upfirst at $25 per month is a bargain for message taking. It is useless if you need appointment booking. Match the service to your actual needs.</p>
<p><strong>2. Ignoring setup and training time.</strong> AI answering services need training. You must input your business details, services, pricing, and policies. A poorly trained AI gives wrong answers and frustrates callers. Invest 2 to 3 hours in setup during the first week.</p>
<p><strong>3. Not connecting your calendar.</strong> An AI answering service that cannot book appointments is just an expensive voicemail system. Connect your Google Calendar, Outlook, or scheduling tool on day one.</p>
<p><strong>4. Forgetting to review transcripts.</strong> AI is not perfect. Review call transcripts weekly to catch errors, identify common questions, and refine the AI's knowledge base. This 15-minute weekly habit improves performance significantly.</p>
<p><strong>5. Expecting AI to handle everything.</strong> AI answering services excel at routine calls. They struggle with complex disputes, emotional customers, and highly technical questions. Have a human escalation path for those scenarios.</p>
